    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "A \"test run\" sounds a bit risky if a tech journalist starts digging into the logs. If they see it was actually just an open S3 bucket, we're dead. Is there a way to frame it more as a technical anomaly or something related to our latest system updates instead? I want to avoid any mention of \"misconfiguration\" even in a positive light.",
